76561198020728468,Recommended,269210,32223848,Posted: 6 June,all,Gerard,"I think this game might be suffering from review bombers, or otherwise people just didn't know what they were buying.The main complaint of all these negative reviews seems to be that the game is boring. I just want to make sure we're all on the same page here, it says Hack 'n Slash and ARPG right there in the tags. Have any of you even played an ARPG before? They are the most boring, repetitive games on the market outside of MMORPGs. Diablo 2 is the game that codified 'Doing the same thing over and over but with different colors and bigger numbers'. Hero Siege explicitly models itself after that and you mean to tell me it's too boring for you?The other recurring complaint seems to be some gibberish about the ingame shop. It's there, I guess. Just like the game itself. Besides Diablo 2 it takes strong cues from Binding Of Isaac, even copying some of the item upgrades. It's an allright game, for 1,50 euros I can't get very flustered about it either way."
