76561198081450332,Not Recommended,269210,17040941,"Posted: 14 July, 2015",all,Iso Koala,"The game gave me a good first impression. Graphics are not great, but good enough especially for the price. The characters all seem quite interesting, and are more original than common fighter/mage/thief classes in many games. I wanted to try all of them!When you start to play the game, you will be faced with some very basic issues right away though. Some of them so simple, that you wonder if they tested the game at all. For example, in local coop, player 2 can talk with people, check his inventory, etc... but he cannot quit those menus! Player 1 has to cancel all actions player 2 started. Beside such silliness, game is full of major bugs. Enemy attacks crushing you inside wall so you have to restart the game, your character teleporting below the game field, items disappearing in coop play every time you die but reappearing when you enter new area (this is not a feature, its obvious bug), etc. Most of them are not just bugs, but common functionality issues that should be working before a public release.Game has good sides too. Getting items is catchy, it has huge ammount of relics and powers, large ammount of different enemies etc. Fields are varied in graphics and styles.Yet, AI, enemy attack patterns and animations are all quite basic and lame. You cannot really dodge majority of attacks. Its not skill based combat, but DPS fight based on the items you have. And when you get few good items, or only even 1, the game becomes a cakewalk from an impossible. A single piece of good equipment can easily give you more stats than leveling your character to level 100 will, and you can get such item in few minutes of play, no kidding.All said, the game is cheap and still quite enjoyable in coop. Id give it a nice B- and a thumb for a good effort. I would be able to look past some of the problems, for the low price of the game and probably inexperienced developers.Yet, the worst problem of the game is something I dispice so much, that I regret the day supporting these greedy mobile phone developers. You don`t buy the whole game when you buy this, you buy part of it. You have to buy the rest in DLC`s. I am not even a hater of DLC`s . They are usuallly a good way to add more to a good game. But the way DLC is implemented in this game, is the system from those lousy mobile games. There is no closure to the game unless you buy all DLC`s. You never face the last boss or enter all the areas in the game, even though those are displayed in the field and in the menus. They are displayed to tease you to buy more. This is not even an issue about money. I woudn`t complain if the game costed 2X the ammount it does now, and woudln`t require DLC`s. It`s the bad aftertaste I got from the system the game abuses that makes me angry.For a less greedy, more polished, bug free, more skill based game of similar style, go buy Hammerwatch, if you don`t have it allready."
