,Not Recommended,269210,32740683,Posted: 24 June,all,Eromivus,"Bottomline:This game truly had a lot of promise, but the developers are their own worst enemies. They're breathtakingly unprofessional, and the game is still being designed. If you're expecting a finished, definable game, do not buy this.Expanded:I know if you're reading this you're primarily wondering whether or not the game is fun. Unfortunately, in this review I'm instead forced to discuss the developers, as discussing the game is almost pointless. You see, every time I check back in hoping I can finally enjoy a finished product—a product that hasn't been in Early Access for years—I instead find the game has either been broken by another ad hoc patch (likely a hotfix of a hotfix of a hotfix) or fundamentally redesigned. I'm not exaggerating.While I'm not angry and have no intention of being mean here, I think it needs to be said: I can fairly say these are the least professional developers I have ever seen in the gaming industry that are not actively trying to scam you. They're not fraudsters. They're not malicious. They are most definitely comically incompetent. It's almost endearing at first. Their updates read like they decided to provide an update in between a round of shots. No planning, no editing, no self awareness—like you'd expect from someone who has never felt the burden of responsibility.As for the game itself, despite having a very solid game loop there was always the sense that this was an Early Access game searching for its soul. They still haven't found it. The game has gone through several conceptual changes (some quite drastic), and now apparently they're about to release a complete redesign of the game. No joke, it sounds like the entire structure of the game is changing. Hell, maybe it'll even be the best thing to happen to the game—but I no longer care. You'd think after saying ""oops"" for the 50th time a sense of shame and embarrassment would compel them to get their act together, but not so.You can get away with some of this stuff with Early Access, but for a game that has already been released and has multiple DLC's it's simply not acceptable. Please, do not buy this game until the developers grow up and figure out how to deliver a product. Or at least wait to see if the next iteration of the game is something special, which is a ridiculous thing to even have to say."
76561198039087561,Not Recommended,269210,21466764,"Posted: 25 February, 2016",all,Cripplboy,"Trying to be as neutral as possible, I still find myself echoing many of the comments made by others. The game is a fast and fun roguelike with enough customization to be enjoyable without being overwhelming. It's good for a few hours of fun.That said, it has gone through several changes to mechanics since I bought it, some of which affect balance and playability DRAMATICALLY. The mana system complaints are valid; it's frustrating to have high-level characters, into which you have invested much, suddenly become unplayable because their skills cost more than their maximum mana. The changes to skill synergies and itemization also significantly changed the game, though some may appreciate the changes. I enjoyed the speed of the game...the changes have increased the depth, which some players may like, but the game has lost its easy-going charm to me.All that to say: the game has been fun in the past, and may continue to be so. Be aware, though, that MAJOR changes have come since release, and may continue to come, that may completely change your enjoyment of the game.I have not have any contact with the devs, so I cannot comment on professionalism."
