,Not Recommended,269210,20257957,"Posted: 3 January, 2016",all,Japonês da Federal,"Here, my opinion after going through a couple giga-threads about the game:From me: I like the game. I love the style and the mechanics. I am such a sucker for roguelikes and random generation, and that may have biased me into getting the game. Single-player was crazy good for me, and that was enough. I started delving in the community and the forums to see if the DLCs were worth my pennies.There are some major, glaring flaws in it: multiplayer has been a problem since launch and I never bothered playing online because it is buggy and devastatingly disappointing; the mana mechanic is well intended, but it is not balanced yet (there is a reason most successful roguelikes adopt cooldowns, skills are the best part of every character); some new items lack in the originality department and in more than one occasion the devs were disgustingly rude to the community.I could care less about Multiplayer. I gave up on that front. This game would be lovely with friends, but there are too many problems in the execution of it.Mechanics: I have my own bickering with the mana resource and with the amount of points allocated with every level, and I think it is not the optimal approach to the game. I usually leave attribute points unallocated because they don't even matter when compared to item and potion bonuses and onuses (eg. -40 strength). I hope this gets reworked soon.But that all was ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ for me - I like the game and single-player, even with these flaws, made me happy. I like that experiments are being made to the game and, even when they are not well-implemented, it gives the chance of growth and evolution! To learn from mistakes made and get the good parts of it in other iterations! I love the new animations for the enemies!What killed the game and the possibility of buying DLC for me was a thread where a dev answered one of the many call-outs to the flawed mechanics with irony and disrespect. ""boohoo mana boohoo equipments stop crying"".No. This is NOT OK! There is no ♥♥♥♥ing reason for this ♥♥♥♥ing nonsense of disrespecting the fanbase that is playing a game that is in the same genre and niche of several better indie roguelikes! Risk of Rain, Nuclear Throne, Rogue Legacy, Eldritch, A Wizard's Lizard, Cardinal Quest, Teleglitch, even ♥♥♥♥ing Rogue Shooter! FTL gave for free a major update that revamped and added things to the mix! Devs for most up-and-coming indies are constantly listening their fanbase and testing things before making gameplay changes! It is NOT OK to just fall down and ♥♥♥♥ on your fans! I will not support this!I know many of the players share my POV. And I hope the devs get down from their high horses and start listening to the community that supported and helped the game get on the limelights. This is a good game for those who like to grind and to be merrily repeating stages, and has potential! But I would not recommend it to anyone now.I'm really sorry. I'm terribly disappointed."
