,Not Recommended,269210,16283924,"Posted: 9 June, 2015",all,Notesurfer,"Hero Siege combines the gamefeel of Gauntlet with the combat mechanics of Binding of Isaac. While the gameplay at its core is solid enough, Hero Siege has some very rough edges. Multiple currencies and an impossible-to-afford item shop reek of a bad mobile pay-to-win port, while an unconscionable number of assets are lifted verbatim from the games that supposedly inspired this one. Hero Siege goes beyond homage to straight-up theft, and for this alone it cannot be recommended.Still, the many unique classes and multiple difficulty levels offer a lot of replayability, and there is a unique sense of frantic and overwhelming odds which will push the player to build the most efficient character possible. For those who love grinding through waves of enemies and have no qualms about the use of stolen assets, Hero Siege will definitely offer a few hours of fun. For others however, the repetition will quickly accumulate into manifest boredom."
