,Recommended,269210,13780168,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,JakeArtistIV,"Been Playing the Hell out of this one since I bought it during the Winter Sale of 2014, its Basically a combination of a Horde mode and Binding of Isaac since the Items you can get are pretty much the same (even the names) Takes you through 5 Whole Chapters with 5 stages in each. so 25 levels in total, complete with optional Dungeons, Crypts, and Shops to go to between Enemy Waves which you must survive around 6 to 8 waves per stage. with the final wave of each stage being a mini boss. Now the game does have a lot of replayability. lots of characters to go through and can grind your way all the way up to level 200 I'm sure. but it does get pretty damn stale at times. since you basically just kill wave after wave after wave of enemies for hours on ends. until you reach the end of a Chapter to fight a Real Boss and proceed until you complete the game.Now this took me a while to figure out, but if you want to succeed in this game in one go. Grab everything in sight, break every possible thing in the level. That means use all types of Potions so you know which ones to use throughout your run, break leaves and pots for cash, and go through Dungeons and Crypts for free items or gold at the end of each one. Without doing so the game will be a Hugh Pain in the♥♥♥♥♥ enemies will start to be very difficult to kill and you will most likely die in one or two hits if you are not careful. and the game is FILLED with bugs and glitches. some that can help you, and some that can♥♥♥♥♥♥you off.Overall the game is Pretty damn fun if you want to spend a lot of time playing a game for a good grind. but its really hard at first, and The Melee Characters are almost useless. but once you get a crap load of items the game is pretty simple at that point, even on harder difficultys. So Yeah Give it a shot if it interests you"
