76561198052716059,Recommended,269210,16642713,"Posted: 23 June, 2015",all,Fat Orange Cat,"This game is basically like Binding of Isaac but with slightly different gameplay. Instead of rooms, you are placed on a smallish map. Instead of collecting items, you collect relics. Instead of taking pills to increase/decrease stats, you drink potions. There's a shop on every map, altered versions of enemies (miniboss versions, ones that are immune to attacks, they are different colour too), there's a boss at the end of every map, you get to choose from several different characters when playing and about the only thing that isn't the same, is the levelling system with attributes and talents. And the fact that you have to complete Act's.I played as the Nomad character (Lvl 64 atm) for my first and only character. I was flicking through some threads just before I made this review and apparently it's one of the weakest, if not the weakest, class to play as. I couldn't get passed Act 1 for about 20 deaths. I was about to give up but then I discovered that there's a shop on the map and since that run-through, I beat normal mode and I'm also about to beat Nightmare mode. Managed to level about 50 levels and I've collected around 50 relics so far in one run. People who have mastered this game are probably laughing at that but it was a real game-saver. It really made me feel like I was getting somewhere in the game.Overall, I would recommend this game to anyone who loves rogue-like and RPG styles of gaming. Although it's not really RPGy, the levelling system adds a cool aspect to the game and since I loved Binding of Isaac, this compared nicely. Been playing for about 3 days straight now, dropped all other games.Bottom-lineGet Hero Siege. And Binding of Isaac."
