,Recommended,269210,21991960,"Posted: 22 March, 2016",all,Black Puppet,"So. After a while I decided to give this game yet another shot. The last time, my review was not that kind and it was a downvote. You can clearly see that this it is not a downvote this time.However some points still stand. If not all. Seeing as I deleted my old review without thinking much about the content of the review and saving it I will simply say what I still think is a bad influence when it goes to playing the game.Overall the idea of the game is simple: Survive. You can choose different characters which have different attacks and skills. Some are ranged, some are close combat. And from here it goes directly into the first part of the game. You play on a randomly generated(?) field where there are 4 gates, 1 on every side of the field. The monsters move mainly into the field through the gates and it is up to you to defeat them. Sometimes, you can even find Monsterspawners which will spawn Monsters until you destroy them. Over time, and by random chance, mini dungeons can spawn or you can enter shops. The Minidungeons are varied and contain a good amound of stuff that keeps you on your toes. Some stuff can only be reached by walking through spikes that hurt you and on a low level that will kill you pretty fast. But this, walking through spikes to reach what you want, is optional. Because most of the time the dungeons themself have a beginning and end point. Everything in between is either optional or required to move further into the dungeon. And when you reached it one out of two things will wait for you. A miniboss, with the reward when you defeated him, or a direct reward for reaching the end of the dungeon.And what happens when you leave the dungeon? The game continues on the field as if nothing ever happened. Go and survive until you reach the sixth wave. Because on the sixth wave, your spawnpoint will spawn a servant of Hell (as I like to call it) that tries its best to kill you. But dont worry. Most of the bosses can actually be defeated easily when you are standing next to the spawnpoint when he spawns. Put one of your abilities down, wait for it and he is defeated. Or you can do it the hard way and maybe get killed the first times you play it with a new character. And if you killed this boss you get rewarded with a special item and a portal to the next field.But before I forget to mention it, there is also another thing that happens. Item drops. And I waited until now to mention the reward for killing bosses or clearing dungeons. During your gameplay you will be able to collect items. These items can be special items from bosskills or dungeons or regular Armor to stuff out your character. While I dont see a big difference with armor I can see it with the special items. They give you abilities or just enhance your current stats. Like a Burger that gives you 7k health. Pretty good if you are struggling with the monsters. Or you get the Shiv, which is a active Item that shoots out Daggers(?) and damages enemies in their way. So it is similar to Binding of Isaac. And yes I am making this comparison for a reason, because this game reminds me of Binding of Isaac atleast in terms of Special Items and what they can do for your character.But now we have reached the point of where my old review comes into play. My old review was about this game being bad, a game that I wouldnt recommend at all. While I still stick with, ""I dont really like it that much"", I cannot truly say that this game is bad. It may, or may not be enjoyable and for what you get, there is a lot to do. But now lets head on to what I have said before and what is still a problem for me in the game.1. First Timers DeathThe first time you will play this game, and that means that you have never played it before, you will die fairly quickly. Even going back in you will die fairly quickly again. Of course this has to do with figuring out how to play mostly but some of it doesnt. For a person that never played this i was a bit frustrated at first because of the sudden deaths of mine. Mind you that was in an earlier version of the game but it hasnt changed. The game is difficult, which is good and bad at the same time.2. Difficulty = HitboxWhen playing this game, the hitboxes of Monsters, and yourself seems off. I am saying this because a Skeleton or Rat have hit me when I was 10 pixels away from them. And this varies. Mostly downwards, yet it happens. I have died multiple times to a skeleton hitting me while it was not even able to reach me. And that is a problem. A problem I am sure they will take care of.3. Difficulty = randomThe game is difficult on its own, but it also is spawning in various traps and objects over time. I have noticed many times as to how new traps like Autocrossbows fell from the heavens down on the field. And if you dont pay attention because ""THERE IS LIKE 50 OF THEM! WAAAH!"" it can end up killing you.4. Difficulty = ""Watch out""Every enemy in the game, if big or tiny, if boss or elite can be killed fairly quickly. But as mentioned above, if you are a first timer you will die fairly quickly. Especially when reaching the second field. One of the enemies is a maggot that spits acid and you and damn, if it does not hit you and gets stuck on the floor for about 5 seconds. Dont walk on it or you take a ton of damage. The problem with this is that it caused me to die also a few times because I was focusing on the enemies upfront. Like the 50 enemies I mentioned above. A random maggot spits, or an elite makes a round house spit and you can get dunked on pretty fast.The other points, one being ""DLC for Online Multiplayer"" have been resolved. It was meant to be tested but they wanted to give people the chance to use it anyways, even in the most unstable build. You could say that it isnt worth for a DLC but, eh. It was their decision, and not mine.So far the game is ok. Its not good, it is not bad and it most certainly not a personal favorite or the best game I ever played. Undertale got that spot. No other game gets that. But jokes aside it wouldnt even be a close second. My point is: I dont like this game. However it is a game that people atleast have put effort into and a game that is decent enough to be played. And who knows: Maybe most of the mentioned points above are just me being an idiot ingame.But that is about it. Thanks for reading."
,Not Recommended,269210,14211876,"Posted: 28 January, 2015",all,みoƦƦoƦ ₣o父,"Hey everyone and this is my review about the game!This is a Hack and slash  game.Interface/Menu/SettingsYou can play this game in fullscreen or windowed mode.You can only change the resolution size in windowed mode.You can toggle the music.There is a master volume slidebar available.You are able to play this game with the xbox controller. (Recommendable).You are able to change the controls.There is local play and online multiplayer.You will need a gamepad in order to play a local game.About the game.The game concept is really simple. You go into an arena and you kill enemies. Sometimes there will be rewards or hidden dungeons to be found. Completing them will give you a reward. It's a bit repetitive, if you think about it. You get thrown into a pit. You kill enemies. You clear them wave for wave until you reached the last wave. You kill the boss and you basically redo this but then in different themes. There are also items and you can level up. But the game doesn't really feel rewarding and the mechanics are plain.There are many save slots available. 18 slots.You can customize your character and unlock new items.Able to toggle Hardcore mode.Game is super repetitive.There are multiple different classes. Some can only be purchased with real money.There are no unlockable classes.You are able to change the difficulty.You have a minimap.Other things.Has references from different games.-------------------I Give this game a 6/10"
