,Recommended,269210,30502741,Posted: 13 March,all,Rebel Sketchy,"Hero Siege, where do i start.First off, i found this game a while ago and wasn't very interested in it because of the price, graphics and looked like a cheap knockoff of Diablo 3.A few days ago i saw it on sale for $0.99, so i went and bought the 4 pack for $1.99 and gave 2 copies to my gaming friends. We tried it, one of them lost interest in about a hour and half of gameplay, while me and another friend somehow got hooked to this game even with it's really bad start.What do i mean a really bad start? Well in the 2 hours of trying the game my friend and i came across 3 bugs that really made us wonder if we should sink time into this mess. The biggest bug being when we did a puzzle and when i hit the reset button my friend the was next to the wall and standing on where the stone piece resetted, he got pushed out of bounds and couldn't do anything but walk around and watch me for the rest of the dungeon. Another being sometimes missions sometimes have a tendency to spawn objective items (even mobs and loot that you cant reach) outside the map and you just have to sit there looking at it, although going to the next stage of the act will respawn the last piece for the mission.With that said, you'd think to yourself, this game seems so broken, why would i ever play this? Well, the answer my friend is the grinding and loot that you would normally get in diablo, just a bit more rampaging bloodshed than diablo.Here are my pros and cons:Pros:-Fun if your into one shotting everything from 1-150-Your friend can join you (my friend made a new character and i brought him through Inferno difficulty and got him to 70+ in levels)-LOOT-Neat and useful, sometimes funny relics (#StickmanSteveForMVP)-Classes are for the most part distinctive in playstyles-You can play with up to 3 other friends in a PRIVATE AND OFFICIAL SERVER (yes pls)-You can also host an open server for people to join (good luck getting people to)-You can name your character anything, and you can reset your skills, talents and even rename your character for an ingame currency called rubies.-There's a leaderboard for Wormholes (endgame stuff)-There's a chat section you can talk to people while you wait for your slow as hell friend to turn on what feels like his 1998 windows computer, get his dial-up running, and spend forever getting on skype and finally the damn game.-There are many difficulties to go through while you level up which includes, Normal, Nightmare, Hell, Inferno, Agony, Destruction, and Toxic. Right now my paladin is level 145 and im finally moving to Destruction to hopefully get to 150.-The devs seem to care at least a little bit about the players which is good enough for me.-And most importantly, they have the best relic, Stickman Steve. His quotes are amazing, and his voice is that perfect type of annoying that you'll love.Cons:-Many glitches, but can be fixed by going to the next section of an Act (The game is divided into Act 1-7  and Chapters 1-5 for each Act)-Your items not appearing when you get ingame (which ONLY happens if the server is down and you connect on peer-to-peer, since the items are saved server side, until the server is back up, you have no items)-Server crashes happen 3-4 times in the past few days, but the devs said ti was because alot of new players joined and it crashed the servers, so they are upgrading it over the next little while to hold more players-The damn animation for picking up potions that end up getting me killed once. At least there is a relic to insta-pickup items so it cancels the animation for picking up potions and relics.-Dying resets ALL the relics you collected (when your playing with 1 or more people this only occurs if both/all players die.-You only really need to put your skill points into health as items will increase your skills for you and Damage/Mana has an awful scaling per point you allocate to it, so it is only beneficial to allocate them into health.-There is only one active guild i see on US that has a decent playerbase, and that is 3G, although i've made my own guild with just my friend and i, and we're having fun playing as the underdogs.Overall, as bad as this game looks, i kinda have fallen for it. If your like me and dont mind the grind, even if it's 150 levels and like 6-7 playthroughs of the same maps and Act bosses, you should give this game a shot, especially if its on sale. And if you see me in chat (The Boss), feel free to join my guild or to start up a convo, cause we both know i'm just waiting for my 1998 windows, dial-up, slow as hell friend to finally get on."
