76561198025183655,Not Recommended,269210,9199720,"Posted: 20 February, 2014",all,cityofangels418,"my overall gloss on this game is that it probably isn't worth your time.  it's an entertaining enough premise, but it has a number of flaws, all of which will ultimately frustrate you enough to abandon the game:1. the stages are so loaded down with foreground effects and obstacles, especially in the first stage, that you will frequently die because you have been mobbed and are trapped behind a tree or bush.  it's additionally impossible to anticipate what objects will be passable, and what will be impassable.2. you will take damage from enemies or traps 2-3 times per second, such that an ill-timed trap can knock out 1000 points in 1 second.  i have been instant-killed by traps when i had upwards of 3000 health.3. following on the previous point, stat bonuses and point allocations are phrased with different language--thus, stats seem utterly arbitrary, especially speed and swiftness.4. this game suffers from an enormous inconsistency in its traps, especially the volcanos.  in the snow level, volcanos are naturally occurring, and seem to throw projectiles an arbitrary distance, and with an arbitrary splash damage.  expect to be hit for a ridiculous amount of damage when you are far away from a projectile, and escape when you are unreasonably close.  this problem is exacerbated by the aformentioned foreground effects problem.5. dungeons/crypts/statues used to appear frequently--now they appear only very occasionally, and sometimes when it is impossible to access them (for example, at the beginning of a boss round).  similarly, chests and relics still spawn inside walls or areas that are inaccessible.6. tough damage for enemies is ridiculously high, especially considering that all but two classes are melee.i want to enjoy this game.  the mechanics are simple, and the concept is good.  but it still needs a lot of work, and the frequent updates have only created an inconsistent environment, especially regarding traps and dungeons."
