76561197970242268,Recommended,269210,13233848,"Posted: 4 December, 2014",all,Tobrendi,"If you're reading this, you already know the basic gameplay: it's a shmup with RPG elements. One thing that you can't tell from the videos and screen shots is how confusing it can be when you start. You're thrust into the game world with very little explanation, and you have to figure stuff out as you fight and die and die and die. Some people will find this fun (including me, which surprised me) and some people will find this frustrating and quit. It's up to you to guess which category you'll fall into.I haven't experienced any bugs, but I have run into some.. unusual balance decisions. Enemy melee attacks seem to be much weaker than their projectiles, which in turn are much weaker than the projectiles spawned when they die, so you have to be more afraid of enemies when they die than when they chase you. Like I said, kind of odd, but once you notice that pattern and get used to it, it's no less fun.Skills don't look very balanced to me, either, but respeccing is cheap so that's not necessarily a big deal.Graphics and sound are pretty subjective, and you can check them for yourself in the above video, but FWIW I really like them. The one exception is the voice acting, which I didn't think was the 'so bad it's good' type. I thought it was the 'so bad it's really terrible' type."
