,Not Recommended,269210,11680105,"Posted: 12 August, 2014",all,Nonon,"First of all, you get to choose and upgrade your characters, equip them with hats, and when you die you keep your levels gained and thus your ability/stat upgrades as well. The characters themselves are all fairly diverse, with active abilities and different ways to upgrade your regular attacks. As the game is completely reliant on RNG you will definitely have a few ""wtf"" moments where you just die. In a lot of cases getting hit once or twice is insta-death. The tombs and crypts are usually so hard that I just ignore them. Some of the bosses are stupidly easy and some are nearly impossible with certain classes.The creativity factor is there. The enemies are fairly generic but the designs and sprites are not bad. The voice acting is unimpressive. Personally I have beat the first area boss (which is a random boss each time of course) several times but upon reaching the second area I just get overwhelmed and shortly die, every time.The game is fairly fun. I play it from time to time and I got it on sale for cheap. A week or two after I got this game they released the DLC which basically says ""Buy our DLC for $6 or you won't get any updates"" and it's a slap in the face. Another reviewer said that he noticed some of the artifacts are stolen straight from Binding of Isaac. I would say that this game is definitely worth buying if it's on sale, and i'd say to wait until the DLC goes on sale if you plan on buying it. If you want to support a real action roguelike, go check out Nuclear Throne."
