,Not Recommended,269210,21829771,"Posted: 13 March, 2016",all,Stungun,"Bought this a while ago, I think when it was on sale. Finally got around to playing it over a year later. What I found was a bunch of locked content barred behind DLC doors, a painfully difficult start (my first few runs died in the first minute of gameplay until I was finally able to find some equipment), no ingame explanation of how to even play, and a glaring UI bug -- the numerical portion of your health gauge doesn't change no matter how much damage you take. (The actual bar works, and the mana gauge works fine, but not the numerical part of the health gauge -- it always reads full) Seriously, that kind of a glitch indicates nobody's ever even bothered to playtest this thing. Then there's also rat nests spawning outside the reachable gameplay area. And then there's the fact if you get unlucky with a statue early on, you can take a -40 penalty to Strength, which can make it gonegative-- and moreover, make yourdamage output become negative. That's right, your main attackheals enemieswhile you're below 0 Strength.It's also rather chilling to see the first five reviews on this page being all negative, and three out of five of them blaming the developers for being vindictive, deleting criticisms from the forum, and even banning said critics from both the forums AND the game's multiplayer -- all for the supposed purpose of maintaining their 'motivation'. This is very bad PR, and bad PR leaves permanent black marks on a developer's reputation. Far worse than losing motivation for working on a single game, as that reputation can carry over to future created games.Also... is it just me or are there a lot of ripped ideas fromThe Binding of Isaacin this game? I'm seeing too many similarities for it to be mere coincidence or marked up to 'inspiration'.It's kinda fun although parts of it are on the tedious side, but I'll play it because I've already paid for it. But for most players I would advise agains