this game for a good year and they haven't fixed it. The servers also seem like they got worse. You rage quit harder, and consider uninstalling, but you most likely enjoyed the singleplayer so you held onto it and waited for the next time you had literally nothing to do.SO! You got my biased part of the review out of the way. Here's the ""General"" review. I will take each piece of the puzzle and put it together next to a # rating. 1 = Bad | 10 = GoodGameplay - 4: It's fun! It's entertaining and is a nice grindy beat-em-up dungeon crawler/treasure hunter. It's like a discount Binding of Isaac if it had sex with discount Diablo. *Now, that's if you disregard the glitches. But with the glitches, the game just SUCKS. No way around it...*Multiplayer - (Official Server Hosting:2 Peer-To-Peer Hosting:4) The official servers suck so badly. That's all I can really say for that. Peer-To-Peer is pretty much hosting your own server, which for the most part fixes the lag issue to an extent. It at least makes it easier to play without disconnecting so frequently. I know this because I've played the majority with my girlfriend (all the way in Japan and we both still had good connectivity compared to the official server(s).) and we had plenty of fun playing together on there, however we both encountered the bug that makes our gear disappear and our levels drop due to rare auto-saves.Bug Free/Playability - (BF:1 Playability:*3*) Oh damn. It's bugged alright. *It is playable but....the glitches really ruin the mood as they're so frequent.* Nothing more to really add, just saying if you can ignore the mere gear/relic/level deletion, it really isn't that bad.Intruiging - 3.5: Honestly, I can't say it's boring at face value but it's definetally not attractive. I'll probably play it for 30 minutes then get off and do something else. But it's something I'll always come back to once in awhile, and maybe with my friends.Story - There isn't any. Unless you count slashing through mobs and randomly killing bosses as ""story"".DLC - (*) I haven't bought any DLC however some accessories and characters are locked behind them. I can't make even a biased review on them because I honestly don't really want to buy them. Technically, I'd rate the DLC at 1 from face value as I'm not really intruiged by any of the other characters. *The fact that they are being so rude to their customers and deciding to not fix bugs, in essence making the game a mere cash grab. Seriously. Just don't waste your money or time.*Community - 2: They are either silent or illiterate kids being angry in the lobby chat. If you're going to play, just go P-T-P with a friend.Overall - *1*: *This game is a nightmare. It's a wreck. It's a ruin. It's a cash grab. It's so. Very. Bad. I'm so sad that I can't get a refund so I don't have to fund the creators deciding to make such terrible broken games that are mere cash grabs, scams. I'm going to refund the gift I gave to my girlfriend so I can buy something else that's better and put heart into, even if the game is only 5$. Don't support the company until they learn to actually fix their coding.*"
