,Not Recommended,269210,33262490,Posted: 4 July,all,truthd,"TLDR: Mobile port, that really punted on PC keyboard/mouse controls, and poor UI decisions. Underneath that is a find little roguelike ARPG (minus any storytelling...)Let me start by saying I think this is a pretty fun game. Imagine Diablo has a baby with a roguelike, but if you're a PC player the port from mobile to PC is just terrible. TERRIBLE. I can't stress how annoying it is to be unable to use your mouse while looking through your inventory, or the fact that items don't show their stats on the item. Your mouse works in most places, but imagine filtering through all the loot in a game like Diablo, but you can't see the stats of anything unless you use the keyboard to select each item and then click G to preview it. There is no reason the stats couldn't be displayed right on the item without having to preview it, and there is no reason I shouldn't be able to select an item and equip it with my mouse.This is the worst port I've come across on steam. There is no excuse for how inventory is managed in this game. If you can somehow get over that, it's a pretty fun little dungeon hack type of game, but you'll have to deal with a terrible UI, terrible keyboard/mouse controls and very little explanation of what things do and devoid of any story telling. A fun game that is a flop on PC for me, I quickly grew tired of managing hundreds of items in my inventory like I was playing a DOS game from the 80's."
