76561198042721306,Not Recommended,269210,11337862,"Posted: 20 July, 2014",all,Noah Human,"This game is a blend of Diablo 2 and The Binding of Isaac, or, in other words, Hack 'n' Slash with Rogue-like elements. What I'm getting at is that it's got randomized enemies, dungeon-crawling and gold hoarding like from an old Diablo game, yet it has randomized ""pills"" (potions) and gameplay-changing relics as seen in The Binding of Isaac. I like it. The game is also light in content, meaning that it's not supposed to be taken seriously, e.g. such over-the-top serious voice-acting, that it makes you cringe, etc.Up-sides of the game:+Something new: Hack 'n' Slash meets Rogue-like+Humorous voice-acting (some may disagree with this one)+Randomized enemies, each stage may have different bosses, etc.+Randomized potions, powerful relics+Lots of character classes, each with their own skills and skill-buildsWhat I didn't like about the game is that it didn't have much to offer, as in, all levels were limited to a box-shaped fortress which you couldn't leave, all the gold you hoarded gave you little help (you may ocassionally buy a Full-Restore potion, which is by far the best use for gold, or buy an AttackSpeed-Boost potion to help you take down a boss quicker) but I'd really like to see some other use for the gold I gather rather than just spending it on potions. The game also has lots of grinding to get the higher levels of your character, and when you eventually get strong enough, the early levels become a total bore.Down-sides of the game:-Little use for gold-Game is a grindfest, but you overpower your foe fairly quickly-Boring base levels (Dungeons and Crypts are a bit more random)-Game doesn't keep giving you fresh content for longOverall I'd give this game about 5.5/10, it's pretty ""meh-diocre""My advice, if you sometimes need to waste a couple a' minutes and see this game for a cheap price, get it. Otherwise? No. I don't think buying this game will pay off as you won't play an hour for every buck you spent on it buying it full-priced."
