,Not Recommended,269210,15646029,"Posted: 1 May, 2015",all,Regardless,"Overall, the game needs extreme balancing and polishing.As far as the pros go, it's relatively fun to run around killing monsters. However, nothing really feels particularly remarkable or original. Things start off incredibly slow and you'll soon find yourself more annoyed by the traps, monsters, and game in general than immersed in it.The classes feel astoundingly unbalanced. And although you have several (not a huge amount) of passive and active skills to dump your talent points into, many feel severely underwhelming or just make no sense, such as the necromancer's talent to buff all summons improving each summon more than the individual summon talents themselves.You also have the choice of dumping points into Strength, Swiftness, Armor and Stamina, though you'll soon find there's no point in anything but Stamina to avoid being instagibbed. That said, you'll still get instagibbed after hundreds of waves, most likely by a trap which can be astoundinly overpowered. The majority of your character progression is through relics which you have a chance of grabbing after bosses, from chests or short dungeons and you can stack up a large amount to run through enemies, but they're easily lost as you only have them for that particular run and getting instagibbed is easy which leaves you to start off terribly slowly.With regards to relics, some have terribly useless descriptions and there's no way I've found to even look at the description after you've picked them up. Other items that are permanantly worn are picked up on a ""discard or replace and discard worn item"" basis, with the discarded items simply disappearing. That said, the game doesn't pause when you're picking up items, which has caused me to lose a significant upgrade when being attacked by a monster when picking up an item and having to immediately cancel and discard the item. Traps also still remain after an area is cleared which can just make checking the loot a pain when things are still shooting at you.Many of the sprites also appear rather half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥as well as things like ""puzzles"" in dungeons which generally consist of walking around stepping on buttons or pulling levers and feel like a complete waste of time.Also seeing a class in the opening video you'd like to play then buying the game and realizing you have to buy DLC for it is kinda bogus.You can have fun with this game, it's just not worth it."
