76561197999737264,Not Recommended,269210,19108949,"Posted: 15 November, 2015",all,gary,"I used to really enjoy this game, a bullet hell brawler with punishing difficulty but not too long ago I loaded up my lvl 150 pyro to find they've changed the game so much that I don't find it fun anymore.It used to be that loot dropped and you would have to either wait until the end of the wave(s) to decide whether to equip it or do it during battle.  Instinct told you whether an item was better and you would quickly press A or B to decide.  Now you pick up equipment, it's placed into storage and have to go through a tedious process of deciding whether to equip or sell it.  In theory this would work well except that the loot screen doesn't tell you the full stats for the item, some attributes are missing rendering the whole thing moot.  Also money in the game only has use in the shop so selling items is pretty much pointless since you get enough of it during the waves.The change to have an energy bar has destroyed your talents.  Instead of being on a cooldown timer they now have an energy cost and all draw from the same pool.  I can see that they are trying to go for ""carefully pick which one to use at the right time"" but in reality it means that you only try and use your strongest attack the other 3 are useless.  For a pyro this means you get 2 hydras and then have to wait ages to get another as the energy bar slowly refills.  Enemies will sometimes drop energy pills that refill the bar a little but there is so much flak on screen it's difficult to get to them.You can still get insta-killed by acid spitters and other ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t one hits which is the reason why I stopped playing the game in the first place.Everything seems to be a lot easier as well, even with limited hydras I can still trigger all waves and get through with no hassle.The problem is that this seems to be change for the sake of it but it's still buggy and not well balanced.  There are still times when I wonder what killed me.  The relics still aren't explained.  Keys still drop far too infrequently.  Bosses are still way too easy (I haven't checked if you can still farm them by save scumming).  The energy system is a needless addition that prevents you from having ""oh♥♥♥♥♥♥oh♥♥♥♥♥♥quot; moments that spamming buttons gets you out of, it has also made useless 3 of your talents. The new loot mechanics are buggy, needless and add little.  You still can't have local multiple player on multiple monitors (so you can push each other off the screen).  Potions are still a hit and miss affair.  You still get killed by the environment more than enemies and the core game I originally enjoyed has gone.And wtf is a wormhole???  The game could explain these things a LOT better."
