,Recommended,269210,20270498,"Posted: 3 January, 2016",all,wampXs,"The Game is fun, but it has many flaws. First of all, the combination of genres is really cool. It's basically a Beat'em Up + RPG + Rogue-Lite, it definitely has many inspirations from The Binding of Isaac (it even borrows ideas like the bible makes you fly"", ""Book of Belilal, gives you DMG"", and others, plus the way you attack.).Now, when it reaches a certain point, with a certain combination of items, i became a lawnmower with my Viking, destroying multiple waves of monsters in high difficulties alone, with ease.Now, i'll let the flaws come in. Trying to play with friends is a nightmare. You can either port-foward or use Hamachl, but the game constantly crashes, bugs you back to the lobby, many funky stuff that annoys.In a server, you can exit in you don't lose any of your items, so the game is kinda broken there.The sound effects are nice, but most of the voice acting is really unprofessional and distracting, like that Stickman active item that is really weird and badly dubbed.Bosses are ridiculous easy at the beginning, at the point of enemies having equal or more HP than them, and later on bosses have a weird difficulty spike. (Hp barely changes between Normal and Nightmare, there was another one that jumped to Hell where Anubis had like, 500k hp, then on Hell he had 2 or more Million hp.)There is a ridiculously frustrating puzzle in a dungeon where you have to place many crates over buttons (including a line of buttons, it probably sparkles the memories of whoeved did it), where if you don't have any flight it will be a nightmare, the crates get stuck in corners, and any slight touch can move them, so you gotta restart it a lot and it bugged me a ton.And one of the biggest problems are the DLCs. Pratically half of the game content is locked behind DLCs, which are more expensive than the game itself. So yeah, if you're not into grinding through the same levels over and over with increasing difficulty, ready your wallet.Now, is the game worth it? Well, yeah! I had fun with it playing solo, it's satisfying to cut my way through enemies, it has cool mechanics and creative concepts, they only need to improve the game a bit to make it golden (looking at you, servers!)."
