,Recommended,269210,20510908,"Posted: 13 January, 2016",all,Merdball,"Short versionThis is a wonderful quick-fix for Diablo 2 fans, and for the money you'll get a solid deal.  Don't expect an incredibly deep game or story, and don't expect something truly amazing - this won't be a game you keep coming back to years later.  But for what it is, it's a fair deal and it's definitely worth the price.Pros:- Local co-op, always a big plus in my book.- Random loot, random levels, and lots of difficulty options after you ""win"", offering a fair bit of replayability.- The first two DLCs added enough fun that I don't consider them a waste of money (this is rare in my book).- There are a lot of interesting classes out of the box even if you don't bother with DLCs.- You can reset skills, but the cost is high enough to make you have to think about it.Cons:- The loot system feels all wrong to me - by level 50 I'm still finding that my level 20 gear is better than anything I've found since.  I expected something more like Diablo 2 or Borderlands where a white level 50 is far beyond any level 20 item.  It seems like loot level has very little to do with loot quality, which makes the item hunt boring fast.- Does gold ever matter?  I thought D2's gold system was broken....- The game becomes a grind very quickly - I'm not sure I'll bother playing anymore, though I do want to know if loot ever catches up with my level.- There are a variety of annoying bugs, like loot dropping in places you can't reach.  If loot mattered more, this could be tragic.- The game is incredibly non-intuitive.  You really have to work to learn how to play.- There's effectively no story to speak of.- Many skill synergies feel forced and/or meaningless.- Manyskillsfeel forced and/or meaningless."
