76561198026299729,Recommended,269210,20456787,"Posted: 10 January, 2016",all,Shhh No More Tears,"TL;DR Rating:[3/5]  ""Fun but Flawed""-Buy when it goes on saleSo, this game is a Twin-Stick-Shooter that is basically a mash up of Diablo and The Binding of Isaac. It has the persistence of gear you equip that is permanent between deaths, and the rogue-likeness of relics that you collect that add effects or massive stat increases and randomized potions that act on your current run ONLY.Graphics: Solid, vibrant sprites, pretty much what you would expect of it.Sound: OK, the voice-overs are amatuer and the BG music is bland and repetitive, but the sound effects are decent.Controls: Responsive and intuitive, good controller support, but some controler functions overlap in menusDLC Content: Unfortunately, half of the game is locked behind ""DLC"" including later acts and classes. If you are on the fence, buy the base game and try it before you buy the rest.Gameplay: ....Ok here is where things get dicey. I really want to love this game more but....The bugs.... god the bugs... This is a game that has (had?) so much potential but I feel like the enourmous list of unfixed bugs is really holding it back. Many have pointed out that the devs have almost abandoned this game, and it is kinda true. They do still fix things here and there but the backlog of documented bugs is astounding. Some you can exploit to power up, some exploit YOU and ruin your run. This is not an early access game, but if you buy it expect all the things that you would expect of an early access game. Its pretty buggy.Class balance is pretty... unbalanced. It becomes clear very quickly which classes are god-like and which are terrible. That doesnt mean they are un-playable, but dont expect to be on equal footing in the higher difficulties.Multiplayer is one of the main draws of this game, but you will need to port forward to host, and the dedicated servers are restricted to Europe. On top of that, the multiplayer server hub system seems to crash often, and player hosted games can also crash for no appearant reason.Items (relics) are somewhat bland, many are blatent clones of The Binding of Isaac items, some are utterly trash, and some really dont make any sense functionally or thematically.NOW DESPITE ALL THAT... I still like this game. This is a nice little loot-grind shoot-em-up and its fun to play with friends or randoms, you get to feel pretty powerful and awesome when you start getting gear and mowing down dozens of enemies at the same time and there are hella explosions and huge damage numbers. It is definitely fun, but at the normal price it is probably not worth it. It has too many bugs and not enough dev support to warrent a full price purchase. If you like the genre, then buy when and if it goes on sale again."
