,Recommended,269210,24427341,"Posted: 20 July, 2016",all,Premium,"TL:DR - Binding of Isaac and Diablo give birth to something thats not hot indie garbage. 8.5/10.  If you want a good game thats gonna eat some time while being entertaining this is a great choice.Gameplay 9/10 - Twin stick shooter with 4 moves per hero.  Passive relics add flare to basic attacks.  Potions to drink (but not chug like a standard hack and slash - you can only hold one) and active relics to use.Sound 5/10 - Voice acting is the only indie garbage part of this game, it feels like they tried but it just comes across as completely low rent.  The music is a little generic and the actual sound effects are decent but  nothing to write home about.Visuals 9/10 - I really like the art direction in this game.  It isn't lazy like a lot of other indie games that have come out this gen.  Reminds me of actual 16 bit games without being too ""retro""Replay Value 10/10 - The amount of content you get is insane even with the base game.  Each hero has countless hours of play and a large progression road infront of it.  This isn't a game you and your friends are going to completely kill in a weekend.DLC 7/10 - Its good DLC, a little expensive and it fragments the game a bit.  Game could 100% use a gold edition people can buy with all the DLC.  NOTE - I own all the DLC except the shaman class (which I will buy after I finish my other runs lol).  The game shines with all the DLC, but the cost of entry is a little high for an indie game.Overall 8.5 / 10 - The game is top tier fun, it might not sound the best but it plays great.  There is a lot of DLC and the game could use a gold/complete edition - frugal folks should wait till that or a sale."
