76561198054879920,Recommended,269210,14492880,"Posted: 15 February, 2015",all,RedKirby,"Simple and effective! Game offers a nod to the Diablo and Diablo II line of games and is a fun 2D slash and hack game.Con:1) Buggy as of this review. Crashes can happen with particular levels/characters though they do get patched very quickly.2) NOT a game for purists. Related to one. I have had a non-hardcore character file wiped out on me. Only happened once but it was annoying. There's a pseudo work around since you can easily edit the SP files. I just leveled a new character back to my old character's level in 2 minute and gave him my old charm.3) 2D and VERY simplistic. This may be an issue if you're looking for a bit more. Yes, there are 150+ levels and 4 difficulties, but they can get retetitive.4) Lack of character customization/skill diversity. You have maybe 1-3 skills you'll use for each character and everyone plays the same way in the end game (when you have lots of relics/items). Namely you sit in one spot and spam normal attacks.5) Balancing is an issue. Neither characters nor levels are balanced though the developers are constantly working on it. Based on luck, starting levels can be insanely hard while end acts can be ridiculously easy. Unexpected OHKO can happen. Your milage can vary.6) Nothing original or innovative in this game. If you're looking for a certain WOW factor in your games, Hero Siege won't do it for you.Pro:1) It's Diablo-lite and 2D! Has a sort of active RPG feel. No limit on stats though character skills (called talents) are soft capped to 30 just like in Diablo II. You can boost them with a charm though. Your character will effectively be capped at level 80-100 because the exp gain is so slow at that point.2) Actively being updated/improved as of this review. Developers do listen to input.3) Super cheap IF you get it on sale. I picked it up for $2 including DLC.4) Perfect for alt-tab/window screen gaming. Fun breaktime game in-between stressful studying.5) Lots of variety in the in-game items called relics. More being added soon. They can range from hilarious/useless to game-breaking.6) Nice mix of classes. Redneck is hilarious while marksman/pyro may be the easiest to play because of their range and them having pet/static defenses.7) **Multiplayer** in the future. MP is in alpha currently and very, very buggy, but this mode has been promised to all holders of the base game. Maybe something to look for.8) Achievement Hunting. Most of the 100+ achievements were removed recently, but developers said better new ones may be added in the future.Overall a strong recommend for fans nostalgic for Diablo II and looking for a simple slash and hack game. A slight recommendation for everyone else. If you can get it for 50% off or better during some holiday then definitely pick it up and give it a try."
