,Not Recommended,269210,14001149,"Posted: 15 January, 2015",all,soolar,"There's difficulty, and then there's just poor design. This game falls in to the later. Projectiles will generally one shot you, or shave off a massive chunk of your health at the very least. Even an AoE DoT from one enemy type generally takes off over a quarter of my HP if it grazes me for half a second. Almost all deaths are nigh-instantaneous, with no chance for reaction or to learn from your mistakes.Additionally, the game seems to love to spawn certain bosses in a way that they will INSTANTLY kill you the moment they spawn in, with some attack where I have not even been able to determine what is HAPPENING, since I only get to see the boss for a fraction of a second.The levelling all seems to completely ignore generally accepted good game design policies, such as diminishing returns. All of the stats you can invest will make absolutely no noticeable difference at first, so early levels only make you feel any stronger from the talent trees. And many of the skills in the talent trees are incredibly poorly designed for early on as well, such as the pyromancer, which has many skills with a 1% chance per rank chance of triggering when you do a basic attack. So when you first grab the skill, it will basically never make any difference, but eventually, once you have levelled it up to be 100x stronger (since nothing seems to have any sort of diminishing returns?) it will also be triggering 100% of the time.I really wanted to enjoy this, because it looked like exactly the kind of game I had been looking for lately, but I have to say, this is one of the most disappointing purchases I have made on steam."
