76561198165193819,Recommended,269210,15408809,"Posted: 16 April, 2015",all,Phase,"Hello, Everyone, this is my first time reviewing a game, so I'm going to do this as well as I can.I enjoyed this game a lot, and I would recommend it, the 35 hours (so far) of playtime I got from it for 5 dollars (at the time) is totally worth it.Here are some reasons why:-Awesomely fun gameplay with great replayablity.-Classes that are unique in their own way.-Varying enemy types, abilities and skills that keep you on your toes.-Puzzles that range from extremely easy to many tries and you still keep accidently hitting the side of the block and messing it up.-Bosses that are crazy powerful and make your heart race as you might lose your level 19 Marksman in 1 hit.-Great soundtrack.-Amazing assortment of items that each have a special effect.-Interesting skill tree.Right as I bought this game, I also bought all the dlc, and that has been worth it too.So hype for the next DLC to come out, so I will get to play the new class and the new mode.Some downsides about this game have been:-Multiplayer is VERY hard due to having to share items, gold, and potions (but that's part of the fun in my opinion)-Some bosses are so bad that I have to struggle for way too long to kill them, or just die,-Getting 1 shot by nearly every boss, trap, or rare enemy in the game (again, I love a challenge, so this is part of the fun, but just a warning to people looking to buy)-Not that much customization as I would like. (Skill-wise, cosmetics I don't mind too much about, but they are there.)Overall an amazing game, and I would recommend it to everyone, there's a lot of reasons to love this game, and not too many things that hurt the game experience for me. I think it's GREAT to play alone or with friends.Enjoy exploring this game and all it has to offer! :)"
