76561198036233434,Not Recommended,269210,16503194,"Posted: 18 June, 2015",all,hushicho,"I will say one thing I liked very much about this game: no permadeath. Thank goodness one developer can think for themselves and aren't just aping the thing umpteen others latched onto. I also liked the character designs and the customisations that you could put on them. The visual style is an appealing one, and the audio is also really great. The gameplay, however...when others have mentioned it's frustrating, they're not kidding. And it's not the kind of frustrating that really keeps you coming back, it's just annoying and, after a point, boring. The game boasts random, different levels, but I just got the same exact level over and over again, with no differences that I could detect. The bosses are cheap in a boring way, the experience is just...boring. It's boring and frustrating, which are two things that I don't look for in games.Maybe if I enjoyed this genre more, I'd really be into this one, but it doesn't make any impression but a bad one with me. I didn't want it to hold my hand, but it not only didn't hold my hand, it tossed me in with no explanations as to anything. While that can be fine for some, a lack of explanation on essential features like skills and powers really is inexcusable; all you have is an icon, which doesn't really illustrate what it's for. So setting skills is hit or miss...mostly miss, because you don't really know what's going to be useful.And speaking of hits, the hit detection in this game is really questionable. Oh, something's in your general vicinity! I guess it does damage to you. Oh wait, there's something random that appeared from nowhere! Guess you're dead, time to start the whole level over again. Oh, fun. I adore retreading well-tread paths. Especially when I've done it a dozen times before. But it doesn't really even make encounters exciting or fun, just irritating because you do not, in any way, have the ability to take on any and every foe, but of course they have the capability of steamrolling you, or at least whittling you down until you're so bored you either make a crucial error or just quit the game altogether.There's also attempts at 'bullet hell' type scenarios, which only artificially ramp up the game's difficulty, usually in an annoying way, and it doesn't really mesh well with the rest of the game. The whole experience seems to be a 'trying too hard' one desperately tossing in artificial ways of ramping up difficulty without actual thought given to how to make the game more fun and enjoyable. Because it's not. It's the opposite of fun.If you're into the dual-stick shooter type games, check it out. Maybe you'll enjoy it. But honestly I can't really recommend this to anyone. I paid basically $1 for it and I still regret it. This is just not a good or enjoyable game, and I can't see myself really ever coming back to it."
