76561197993255516,Not Recommended,269210,13823197,"Posted: 3 January, 2015",all,Geata,"Picked up during holiday sale when it was < $3. Also ended up grabbing the DLC for < $2 because it has the multiplayer. Its fun in that ""you could die any second game and all the progress is wasted"" way, but the bugs, crashes, errors, and lack of any defined direction limit the ability to enjoy the game to its best potential.Pros:*Concept is great.*Quite a few classes.*Monster abilities are basically ripped from Diablo down to the spinning laser sentry of doom, so if you are familiar with D3, you'll be familiar with what the enemies can do.*Relic system is a good implimentation.*Stationary sprite assets are well done.*Strategic planning and luring enemies into traps is a great idea.*Controls feel solid and responsive, even though your character moves painfully slow.Cons:*Moving sprites have maybe three or four frames of movement and look ridiculous when walking.*Only tutorial is a button layout when you enter the first world.*No explination on what the blue crystals are used for or how they are gained.*Minion shows up in menu, but actually isn't unless you bought with crystals.*Stats are terribly balanced. One stat point gives no recognized value. Its all about staying alive to hoard relics to give stat/ability bonus'.*Stat tree is lacking in variety.*No type of dash/dodge move that could greatly increase strategy and playability.*Only by trial and error will you remember which projectiles (enemy and ally) will randomly pass through walls or actually stop.*No way to know which traps actually hurt monsters or let them pass unharmed.*Relic list in Stats screen is broken and will often detail a different relic that the one selected.*Achievments in Sats screen don't unlock properly and have no details.*Multiplayer only available in the DLC and not base game.*Online play is in ""Early Alpha Testing"" which you ONLY find out when you enter the multiplayer lobby.*You have to create a 3rd party account to access Multiplayer.*Multiplayer crashes often.*Players in multiplayer will often ""desync"" from host and get killed by something only the host can see.*Players in multiplayer will randomly trade stats and even abilities from map to map. A samurai will have his Marksman ally's skills or vise versa.*Studio admits to having serverly underpowered servers that can't handle multiplayer.*You must manually create a port forward entry in your router to allow multiplayer.*Bosses can cheaply kill in one hit with no warning, such as the Tree with spinning skulls.*Dungeons/Crypts give zero room to move around bosses causing instant death in many occassions, such as with The Tree w/Spinning Skulls boss.*Feels much like an Early Access title that still has a lot of polish.Final thoughts: Good potential, but overwhelming bugs and cheap deaths by traps hidden by trees and bosses sour the experience. Characters need more fleshing out in both ability and stats. Multiplayer is a pipe dream right now and should be considered highway robery that you have to purchase ""DLC"" to even get it."
