76561198045244712,Recommended,269210,20739934,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,"The 10,000 Year Old King","Yeah, I just posted a good review post Mana-Update, sue me.But to be frank, I can see why alot of fans are upset about the Mana update. It wrecked ALOT of people's characters due to the new mana stat, causing their skills to be rendered useless. And yes, the new inventory is sloppy, and poses problems.But you also need to know that the devs are still working on this game, unlike Loadout. Maybe they will stop later, or something, I dunno, but at the moment, they are definetly still around working on the game. I mean they posted something on the 22nd, it's not like their last post was 2 years ago.The game itself is fun. You have a bunch of classes to pick from, each has their own skills, you can give them a cute little hat and name them suger♥♥♥♥♥♥if you want. You run around a big plane with a few obsticals, and you have to kill wave after wave of monsters, and fight a boss at the 6th wave.There are problems, like the many insta death hazards (acid mucas and spikey bouncy balls of death), and the inventory is clunky, but besides that, at least in my opinion, it's still a fun game.Just be warned, don't grow too attached to your character. Updates in this game can easily ruin them. I'm one of the few people who don't mind this, and are just happy to watch as bosses are eaten alive by my skeletons and demonic arm babys. I'm sure there are people really♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥that their level 80 character was ruined by the mana update, but to me, this just isn't the type of game to get attached to a character you've been building up. But really, this game thrives on Rogue-Like elements, while also letting you build up a character. When you die, you lose all temporary stat changes, and relics you found, rendering you to a soft weakling with only your base stats to defend yourself.But that's also a part of the beauty of this game, when a character's stats are lost, ore lost entirely, just build back up again! The leveling is fun and diverse, and there's enough classes to try something new if you're sick of always playing as the same class.If you're new, you might wanna buy it. I mean it's six bucks, what do you really have to lose? Three bags of Lemonheads? It's a fun game, all things considered! Burning sh*t, poison, playing as a flying pygmy demon from hell, if you like RPG's, you might like this.... Also I've never did the multiplayer, mostly cause I didn't want to make an account on some website, but I hear it's broken to f*ck.... So yeah.... Also the voice acting isn't great...Overall, 6.5/10, could use alot of improvment, but still a fun game in the end."
76561198039331475,Recommended,269210,20881696,"Posted: 31 January, 2016",all,Styku,"If Diablo and The Binding of Isaac had kids, Hero Siege could easily be one of them.Perfect for casual playing, lots of fun for all fans of hack'n'slashes.The game is fun to play, it's not exceptionally hard, but at times demands a little more attention. One of the greatest flaws is little variety in combat system. Only few active skills and an active item get borring pretty quickly. The other major bummer is the strange difficulty. Normally, the game is not difficult at all - I got past most of the levels by triggering all of the waves at once and exterminating everything simultaneously, with no troubles at all. But then, from time to time, there happens to be a mob that kills me in a manner of miliseconds. And it's not even a boss, just a champion or some magic monster with modifiers. And Bosses, for that matter, are one of the easiest encounters in this game."
