76561198047035752,Recommended,269210,20285679,"Posted: 4 January, 2016",all,Butcherbird,"REVIEW BASED ON SOLO PLAY ONLY.Highly recommended. Purchased for Xmas 2015. For less than a dollar, and one of my better game purchases of the year.For my 89 cents, I got like five different classes. I can unlock the other five or so if I buy the DLCs, and maybe I will. In the meantime, I've already had 20 hours of fun and I'm only halfway through.Gameplay is how I imagine Diablo 1 would be as an arcade game. You level up your character type with goofy skills, like a pirate shoots huge cannonballs and her capstone skill is a stupid parrot that kills monsters. You level up by clearing maps using W, A, S, D for movement and arrow keys for attack direction, spam spam spamitty. There are (dangerous) side dungeons with monsters, traps, and puzzles of the ""step here and here"" or ""slide these pillars"" varities.You keep skills and items on character death, but your relics, which can be insanely OP, are lost. When I say OP, I mean OP, too, like I had a crown relic that multiplied my damage by 100. So death does sting a bit, and if you're into being a true PC Masturacer, there's a hardcore mode on top of about 5 difficulty levels with names like ""Agony"" and ""Nightmare"". I wouldn't recommend it, though, as the difficulty spikes considerably and without warning. I've been one-shot or close to it many times.To go with those spikes, there are other cons to Hero Siege. It's not stable, for one thing. It crashes each time I quit the game, for example, and crashed my computer once. The UI, while efficient enough, is clumsy for me and I didn't find the option to change the key layout when I went looking. And while the character design (including abilities/weapons as well as appearance) is cool, the maps get repetitive and dull-looking.Overall, Hero Siege has a great game formula and I hope to get at least another 20 hours of amusement out of it, making  my expediture an hour 2.2 cents. I know I'm harping on the price, just seems like other reviewers are expecting too much for what this game costs."
